        	[
	            'suspect_id'   => 6,
	            'interview' => 'INSPECTOR:  Miss Abernathy, thank you for your time today.\r\n\r\nSARAH ABERNATHY:  Of course\r\n\r\nINSPECTOR:  We understand you are dating Brandon, and were hired as the photographer, and newspaper writer for the evening.\r\n\r\nSARAH ABERNATHY:  That’s correct\r\n\r\nINSPECTOR:  How long have you been dating Brandon? \r\n\r\nSARAH ABERNATHY:  About 6 months. \r\n\r\nINSPECTOR:  And had you previously met any of his family or any other guests at the party that night?\r\n\r\nSARAH ABERNATHY:  I’d met his sister Amanda a few times before. Brandon didn’t want me to meet his other family. They have a strained relationship and I don’t even think they are aware I’m his girlfriend. I hadn’t met any other guests at the party before that night.\r\n\r\nINSPECTOR:  Has Brandon ever talked to you about his relationship with his aunt and uncle or his parents?\r\n\r\nSARAH ABERNATHY:  Well, I mean he was devastated when his parents were sent to jail when he was 16. He believes they made a simple mistake and are innocent. His uncle is hard on him, his aunt is cold and distant. He says both are fixated on themselves and don’t help him or Amanda financially or otherwise. I think he resents his uncle taking over the mansion. \r\n\r\nINSPECTOR:  Now Miss Abernathy, as the photographer and journalist, you must have observed very well the behaviors of everyone at the party, no?\r\n\r\nSARAH ABERNATHY:  That’s true.\r\n\r\nINSPECTOR:  Did anything strike you as unusual?\r\n\r\nSARAH ABERNATHY:  (thinks) Well, only that Professor Ives fainted during the party \r\n\r\nINSPECTOR:  Were you also summoned to the lounge by Dr. Cambridge to help with Professor Ives?\r\n\r\nSARAH ABERNATHY:  Yes, I was\r\n\r\nINSPECTOR:  Did you happen to notice if anyone wasn’t present in the lounge, or if anyone was acting strange?\r\n\r\nSARAH ABERNATHY:  No, I didn’t, sorry. \r\n\r\nINSPECTOR:  About what time did Professor Ives faint and then return to the dining room?\r\n\r\nSARAH ABERNATHY: I think he fainted around 9:00 and came back to the dining room maybe 15 or 20 minutes later? He seemed perfectly refreshed.\r\n\r\nINSPECTOR:  Okay Miss Abernathy. Thank you for your time. We’d like to ask your permission to search your home, this is standard procedure in a case like this. \r\n\r\nSARAH ABERNATHY:  Sure, I have nothing to hide.\r\n\r\nINSPECTOR: Thank you!',
