        	[
	            'suspect_id'   => 7,
	            'interview' => 'INSPECTOR:  Dr. Cambridge, thank you for your time. We appreciate you’re a busy man.\r\n\r\nDr. CAMBRIDGE:  Of course.\r\n\r\nINSPECTOR:  We wanted to ask you about the night the painting disappeared. We understand one of the guests, professor Charles Ives fainted at some point. Can you tell us a little about that?\r\n\r\nDr. CAMBRIDGE:  Well, it was around 9:00 pm. We had just finished our coffee and dessert. We all stood up to mingle in groups when the professor collapsed. I checked his vitals. I asked for the rest of the parties help in moving him to the lounge so I could better assess his situation. I recall asking Daniel to get a glass of water for the man, which he did. While Professor Ives took the water, I questioned him about his health – did he have any food allergies or any medical condition that could explain why he fainted. He said none he was aware of. He received a text and seemed agitated, and told us it was probably work related – he said he’s been quite busy at the University. I instructed him to ignore it and rest. His episode did seem a bit out of the ordinary but because his vitals were fine and he was having no trouble communicating, I suggested he take rest in the lounge and rejoin us after sometime. \r\n\r\nINSPECTOR: Lucky for Charles Ives there was a doctor in the house! Can you describe what happened next?\r\n\r\nDr. CAMBRIDGE:  Well, we closed the lounge room doors and retreated back to the dining area. The professor rejoined us, about 15 or 20 minutes later. He seemed normal by then. \r\n\r\nINSPECTOR: How long have you known Daniel Pembroke?\r\n\r\nDr. CAMBRIDGE:  I’d say roughly 10 years? We are neighbors and belong to the same sailing club. \r\n\r\nINSPECTOR: Has he ever spoken about his business? Possible marital difficulties? I think you know what I’m getting at and I’m sorry to ask, but it is my job.\r\n\r\nDr. CAMBRIDGE:  Look, business has been tough lately. Daniel is old fashioned and technology is rapidly changing the business. His partner, Mason is considerably younger and feels he can and should upgrade to meet the changing market. They’ve had some fights recently. As for his marriage, I’ll say both Daniel and Marcia are incredibly driven and career oriented. Daniel has had his suspicions for a while but honestly, Marcia would be well within her reason to have suspicions too. \r\n\r\nINSPECTOR: How about his relationship with his niece and nephew?\r\n\r\nDr. CAMBRIDGE:  Daniel is a good man but incredibly tough on his family and that includes his niece and nephew. He wants Amanda to abandon her ideas and join his company – she’s very talented and he’d be happy to have her work on marketing and advertising. Brandon is smart, but unlike Amanda lacks focus. \r\n\r\nINSPECTOR: You know the situation well and the family well. Do you think anyone in the family could have done this? Or, were any of the other guests acting in way that makes you think they may have played a role.\r\n\r\nDr. CAMBRIDGE: (Smiles) Medicine is my specialty. I think I’ll stick to that and let you make the call on this one.\r\n\r\nINSPECTOR: (Laughs) Fair enough. Thank you for your time, I do apologize for this, but do we have your permission to search your house? This is standard procedure.\r\n\r\nDr. CAMBRIDGE:  No need for a warrant. You may search my home. \r\n\r\nINSPECTOR:  Thank you!',
